and Puerto Rican neighborhood and shows how the resulting racially biased policies caused the deterioration of this once flourishing area.A clear-sighted, unflinching look at one ghetto community, How East New York Became a Ghetto provides insights and observations on the histories and fates of ghettos throughout the United States.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAfrican AmericanszNew York (State)zNew YorkxSocial conditionsy20th century. 0aEthnic neighborhoodszNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistoryy20th century. 0aInner citieszNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistoryy20th century. 0aMinoritieszNew York (State)zNew YorkxSocial conditionsy20th century. 0aUrban policyzNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistoryy20th century. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / City Planning & Urban Development.2bisacsh1 aPiven, Fox, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPiven, Frances Fox.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081478266840uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814783412.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814783412423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814783412/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK